&lt;p&gt;Glossier is a people-powered ecosystem, brought to life by engaging online and offline experiences. In 11 years, we have built an iconic brand that goes far beyond beauty. Our brand is built on trusted emotional connection, empathy, and consistency in how we show up for people every day. We are woven into everyday moments of people’s lives, becoming part of their routines, their self-expression, and their confidence. We are defined not just by what we make, but by how we make people feel and the relationships we build over time. Our north-star values are to be Human, Curious, Playful, and Helpful. We are driven by a shared mission to become the Most Loved Lifestyle Brand in the World.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;VP, Digital Strategy &amp;amp; Growth&lt;/strong&gt; is responsible for defining and leading Glossier’s enterprise-wide digital growth strategy across owned, earned, and paid digital channels. This leader will shape how digital capabilities, customer experiences, and emerging commerce opportunities drive long-term business growth, customer acquisition, retention, and brand relevance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Chief Commercial Officer (CCO), the &lt;strong&gt;VP, Digital Strategy &amp;amp; Growth&lt;/strong&gt; will oversee the strategic direction of Glossier’s digital ecosystem, ensuring alignment between Digital Commerce, Brand Marketing, Technology, Retail, Wholesale, Product Marketing, and Customer Experience. This role serves as the senior-most digital leader responsible for establishing a unified vision across all digital touchpoints, identifying future growth opportunities, and building the capabilities required to support Glossier’s next phase of scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines strong commercial acumen, customer-centric thinking, and digital innovation expertise. They are equally comfortable setting long-term strategic direction, influencing executive stakeholders, and building the organizational capabilities necessary to support sustainable growth in a rapidly evolving digital landscape.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EXPECTATIONS.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and lead Glossier’s long-term digital strategy, ensuring alignment with company growth objectives, customer priorities, and brand ambitions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a cohesive vision for how customers discover, engage with, and purchase from Glossier across all digital touchpoints and channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and evaluate emerging digital commerce opportunities, technologies, platforms, and consumer behaviors that can unlock future growth and competitive advantage&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish enterprise-wide digital growth priorities and investment frameworks, partnering with executive leadership to determine resource allocation and strategic initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the evolution of Glossier’s omnichannel customer experience strategy, ensuring a connected experience across Retail, Wholesale, Digital Commerce, Social Commerce, Customer Experience, and Loyalty touchpoints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Technology leadership to define the digital capability roadmap, including platform modernization, customer data strategy, personalization capabilities, and future-state digital infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion customer-centric decision making across the organization by leveraging customer insights, behavioral data, and market trends to inform strategic priorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the executive sponsor for digital transformation initiatives that improve organizational effectiveness, customer engagement, and commercial performance&lt;/li&gt;
